**Correction made:**

```java
when(mockConstructorConstructor.get(TypeToken.get(DummyAdapter.class))).thenReturn(() -> dummyAdapterTypeAdapter);
```

The lambda `() -> dummyAdapterTypeAdapter` returns `TypeAdapter<DummyType>`, but the mocked method expects an `ObjectConstructor<DummyAdapter>`, i.e., something that returns `DummyAdapter`.

Since `DummyAdapter` extends `TypeAdapter<DummyType>`, the lambda must return a `DummyAdapter` instance, not a `TypeAdapter<DummyType>`.

So change to:

```java
when(mockConstructorConstructor.get(TypeToken.get(DummyAdapter.class))).thenReturn(() -> new DummyAdapter());
```

Final fixed snippet:

```java
when(mockConstructorConstructor.get(TypeToken.get(DummyAdapter.class))).thenReturn(() -> new DummyAdapter());
```

